.TH "batadv_check_unicast_packet" 9 "batadv_check_unicast_packet" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
batadv_check_unicast_packet \- Check for malformed unicast packets
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" batadv_check_unicast_packet
.BI "(struct batadv_priv *bat_priv "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "int hdr_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bat_priv" 12
the bat priv with all the soft interface information
.IP "skb" 12
packet to check
.IP "hdr_size" 12
size of header to pull
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Checks for short header and bad addresses in the given packet.
.SH "RETURN"
negative value when check fails and 0 otherwise. The negative value
depends on the reason: -ENODATA for bad header, -EBADR for broadcast
destination or source, and -EREMOTE for non-local (other host) destination.
